# =============================================================================
# NetLLM / automated_penetration_test — what to track vs ignore
#
# TRACK (upload to GitHub): Python source, config, docs, small tooling scripts.
# IGNORE: checkpoints, logs, datasets, eval JSON, HuggingFace caches, secrets.
# On RunPod: clone repo, upload exp_pool.pkl / HF token separately (not in git).
# =============================================================================

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
dist/
build/
*.egg

# --- Virtual envs ---
.venv/
venv/
env/

# --- IDE / OS ---
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Secrets (never commit) ---
.env
.env.*
*.pem
hf_token.txt

# --- Training & fine-tuning outputs (large) ---
artifacts/ft_plms/

# --- Evaluation dumps ---
artifacts/results/

# --- Offline experience pools (binary; upload via object storage / scp) ---
artifacts/exp_pools/**/*.pkl

# --- Weight files under artifacts (catch strays outside ft_plms/) ---
artifacts/**/*.bin
artifacts/**/*.pt
artifacts/**/*.pth
artifacts/**/*.ckpt
artifacts/**/*.safetensors

# --- Training logs (huge text) ---
**/train_losses.txt
**/console.log
*.log

# --- Jupyter ---
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# --- Optional experiment trackers ---
wandb/

# --- HuggingFace / torch cache (if ever created under project root) ---
.cache/
models--*/
